The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Army hurt by arrest 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     Army hurt by arrest 
                            
	New Delhi, Nov. 6 (PTI): The deputy army chief today said the arrest of a serving officer in a terror case had hurt the prestige of the force. Indian Armys prestige has been hurt after our officers name came up in Malegaon blast case, Lt Gen S.P.S. Dhillon said in New Delhi.         
	Shrikant Purohit, a lieutenant colonel, was yesterday arrested in Mumbai for allegedly supplying money and explosives for the September 29 Malegaon blast.                                                                                                                                                                          
